<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12525] Wrap lines longer than 100 chars</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12525</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After broadening the acceptable long lines in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12523&quot; title=&quot;Update checkstyle plugin rules to match our use&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12523&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12523&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we still end up with ~900 cases of lines over our chosen length.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go through and wrap all of those that are sensible to wrap and then update &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12523&quot; title=&quot;Update checkstyle plugin rules to match our use&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12523&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12523&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a list of additional exclusions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
